<br>
It isn't your place to dictate how I or anybody else chooses to play, we all have fun in our own way. The numerous high levels who stepped on me in one way or another in Perma were probably having fun too. But they were having fun at the expense of others' fun. That's why I was calling them jerks. They weren't cheating or breaking the rules in any way. They were just being jerks.<br>
<br>
And as for your soapbox statement concerning 8 hour camps, it's not as if I was camping the GBS or Fishbone Earring, both horrendously long camps with zero prospect for loot or experience. I gained 3 levels in Perma trying to get those slippers. Heck, I spent 30 hours this past weekend camping Kindle. My wife and I gained two levels (one of them a hell level) and over 2000pp. Next weekend I plan to go back there, and I will continue to do so until either we both get our gloves, or the goblins stop giving us experience. If the latter occurs, we will probably move on to Lower Guk or Sol B and hope to buy or trade for the gloves.<br>
<br>
