<br>
I went to a three-guild, well-publicized raid on my server recently.  It was in a dungeon appropriate for my level, and for the other folks who signed up.<br>
<br>
We show up in the zone to find another guild camping a critical spawn that dropped a key for one part of the dungeon.  This was unreal, as that guild's leader had been personally told of the raid the night before.  What's more on the topic of your thread Nef is that some of the folks camping this spawn were levels 40 and 50+.  These people apparently never shared the spawn all night long, and we had to ask more than once to even be given the key that dropped from the spawn so we could progress through the dungeon.<br>
<br>
Completely uncalled for, completely rude.  Then later on I find out from another member of the offending guild that they were apparently camping the spawn for a drop that would be given to a lvl 26 guildmate who could have easily killed the mob with a just ONE full group of lvl 25-30s.  That really burned me.<br>
<br>
They should have at LEAST shared the spawn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants>Rants !</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
